First Lady Melania Trump visited Necker Hospital in Paris to meet with patients and staff. She then went to the United States Ambassador's residence to give remarks and introduce her husband to military troops, embassy employees, and their families. Melania and President Trump participated in an arrival ceremony with President and Mrs. Macron, followed by a tour of Les Invalides. Melania and Mrs. Brigitte Macron also visited Notre Dame Cathedral and took a river cruise on the Seine, enjoying views of various landmarks. Melania expressed gratitude to President and Mrs. Macron for their invitation and hospitality, and also thanked the employees and families of the United States Embassy. She concluded her day by joining her husband for dinner with President and Mrs. Macron at Le Jules Verne Restaurant in the Eiffel Tower. Melania acknowledged the rich history and culture of France and the historic cooperation between France and the United States during World War I. She also thanked the patients and staff at Necker Hospital and wished them a speedy recovery. The next day, President and Mrs. Trump would participate in a viewing of the National Day Parade in honor of Bastille Day with President and Mrs. Macron.